chastext is a generic text editing tool
It can act as a replacement for sed when you don't need regular expressions
but you still need to change a small part in a plain text configuration file
or source file depending on what options you want.

To make multiple changes to a text file, you would make extra copies by redirecting standard output
with the > operator from the Linux or DOS command line.
Then you can use them as new input files to further transform them.
If you mess up files beyond repair, at least you still have the original file.
